The article discusses the commemoration of Memorial Day and the 50th anniversary of the Vietnam War. President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama will participate in events at Arlington National Cemetery and the Vietnam Veterans Memorial Wall. They will also meet with Gold Star Families. The Federal Government, along with state and local governments, private organizations, and communities, will launch a 13-year program to honor and thank the veterans of the Vietnam War and their families. The program will also highlight the contributions of the armed forces, federal agencies, and the American people during the war, as well as advancements in technology, science, and medicine. It will also recognize the contributions and sacrifices made by the allies of the United States during the Vietnam War.